article.headline: High Point 83, VMI 71
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid had 22 points and 16 rebounds, and High Point used a huge second half to beat VMI 90-71 on Saturday night. Mike Jefferson also had 22 points for the Panthers (12-9, 4-3 Big South), who outscored the Keydets 60-34 in the final 20 minutes to erase a 37-30 halftime deficit. Cruz Daniels had 16 points and Eugene Harris added 14 for High Point, which shot nearly 54 percent, held a 46-25 rebounding edge and overcame 19 turnovers by forcing VMI into 17. High Point has won two straight and four of five. Travis Holmes scored 25 points to lead VMI (10-10, 2-4), which was just 3 for 21 from 3-point range in losing its fourth straight.
